canonical:
  title: 許行殿試箚子
  author: 李詹
  language: lzh
  text: 竊聞會試入格者以年未滿二十五因停殿試今已數月矣我國家取士之法不拘年齒而取其才尙矣且未行擧人年格一定之令是以年未滿者亦與焉非其罪也伏惟殿下許行殿試使已入格得以出身自後一定年格令行禁止未爲晚也
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 許行殿試箚子
  author: 李詹
  language: lzh
  text: 竊聞會試入格者。以年未滿二十五。因停殿試。今已數月矣。我國家取士之法。不拘年齒。而取其才尙矣。且未行擧人年格一定之令。是以年未滿者亦與焉。非其罪也。伏惟殿下許行殿試。使已入格。得以出身。自後一定年格。令行禁止。未爲晚也。
korean:
  title: 허 행전시 차자
  author: 이첨
  language: kor
  text: 가만히 듣자오니, 회시(會試)에 입격(入格)한 자가 연령이 25세가 되지 않는다 하여, 전시(殿試)를 정지하였사오며 지금 수개 월이 되었다 하옵니다.우리나라에서 선비를 뽑는 법은 연령에 구애받음이 없이 오직 그 재주를 얻는 데 있사옵니다. 또 거인(擧人)에게 일정한 연령을 정한 영(令)을 시행하지 않고 있으므로 연령이 차지 않은 사람이 시험에 참가한 것은 그의 죄가 아니옵니다.엎드려 바라옵거니와, 전하께서는 전시(殿試)의 시행을 허락하셔서 이미 입격(入格)한 사람에게는 출신(出身)을 주도록 하옵소서. 금후로 일정한 연령을 정하여 여기에 차지 않는 사람은 금지시켜도 늦지 않사옵니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0590_020_0050&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Memorial Requesting Permission for the Palace Examination
  author: Lee Cham
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I humbly hear that those who passed the Provincial Examination, being under twenty-five years of age, have had the Palace Examination suspended. Several months have now passed in this state.

    Our nation's method of selecting scholars knows no constraint of age—it seeks only talent and merit. Moreover, no fixed age requirement has yet been enacted for examination candidates, and thus those below the required age have participated in the examination through no fault of their own.

    I respectfully beseech Your Highness: permit the Palace Examination to proceed, that those already qualified may receive their posts. After this, a fixed age requirement may be established and enforced. It will not be too late.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The Provincial Examination (會試) and Palace Examination (殿試) were the higher stages of the civil service examination system in East Asia.
  - key: ''
    value: This memorial argues for mercy and consistency in administrative policy, suggesting that retroactive enforcement of age restrictions would be unjust.
